-- Singapore Equity Movers: Cosco, Fraser & Neave, IPC Corp., Olam
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 2012-11-23T09:39:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-23/singapore-equity-movers-cosco-fraser-neave-ipc-corp-olam.html
Singapore ’s Straits Times Index
+0.1% to 2,989.28 as of the 5:10 p.m. local time close. +1.5%
for week. Almost three shares rose for every two that fell on
the 30-member gauge.  Gainers:
* IPC Corp. +15%; co. agrees to investment in 6th business hotel
in Japan
* Cosco Singapore +2.8%; co. delivers converted floating
production, storage and offloading vessel to European customer  Decliners:
* Olam -1.8%, extending this week’s losses after short-seller
 Carson Block  questioned the commodity supplier’s accounting
method; Olam sued Block and his firm  Muddy Waters  in a Singapore
court yesterday and said it has sufficient liquidity to
withstand market stress
* Fraser & Neave -0.3%; Thai billionaire Charoen
Sirivadhanabhakdi has extended a deadline for an offer to gain
control of F&N after a group led by Overseas Union Enterprise
topped the bid last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
